EX PARTE A.M. (In re A.M. v. Colbert County Department of Human Resources) 1150955 Supreme Court of Alabama. April 28, 2017 Carla Putman Maples, Florence, for petitioner. Sharon E. Ficquette, chief legal counsel, and Karen P. Phillips, asst. atty. gen., Department of Human Resources, for respondent. Prior report: Ala.Civ.App., 236 So.3d 81 . MURDOCK, Justice.

The petition for the writ of certiorari is quashed.

In quashing the petition for the writ of certiorari, this Court does not wish to be understood as approving all the language, reasons, or statements of law in the Court of Civil Appeals' opinion. Horsley v. Horsley , 291 Ala. 782 , 280 So.2d 155 (1973).

WRIT QUASHED.

Stuart, C.J., and Bolin, Parker, Shaw, Main, and Wise, JJ., concur.
